# AI Agent Rules

## Git & Version Control
- **Commit Messages**: When generating git commit messages, BE DESCRIPTIVE. Do not use generic messages.
  - Structure: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`
  - Format: Follow Conventional Commits.
  - Detail: Include a body explaining "why" the change was made, not just "what".
- **Pull Requests**: Provide comprehensive PR titles and descriptions.
  - Titles should summarize the main change.
  - Descriptions must include:
    - Summary of changes
    - Key implementation details
    - Testing steps performed
    - Checklist of verified items

## General
- Follow the existing project structure and conventions.
- Ensure all new dependencies are properly recorded in package files.
